name: Dividend 15 Split Corp. II Class A Shares
longDescription: The Companys investment objectives with respect to the Class A Shares are to provide holders of Class A Shares with regular monthly cash dividends targeted to be $0.10 per Class A Share to yield 8.0% per annum on the original issue price and (b) on or about the Termination Date, to pay the holders of Class A Shares at least the original issue price of the Class A Shares. The net proceeds of the Offering will primarily be invested in the common shares or other equity securities of the Portfolio Companies, which are: Bank of Montreal Enbridge Inc. TELUS Corporation The Bank of Nova Scotia Manulife Financial Corporation The Thomson Corporation BCE Inc. National Bank of Canada The Toronto-Dominion Bank Canadian Imperial Bank of Commerce Royal Bank of Canada TransAlta Corporation CI Financial Income Fund Sun Life Financial Inc. TransCanada Corporation.
